Remove the woody end of the @asparagus{1} and cut into 4cm pieces. Cut the very end off the @tenderstem broccoli{1}. Finely slice the @spring onion{1}, separating the white and greens. Peel the @garlic clove{1} and @ginger{1} and finely dice.

In a dry #pan{}, toast off the @cashew nuts{1.5%handfuls} for a few mins until golden.

> As always, watch your nuts closely as they can burn quickly.

Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles and tenderstem. Boil the @egg noodle nests{2} for ~{4%minutes} until just cooked and add the tenderstem for the last ~{2%minutes}. Drain them under cold running water and put back in the pan filled with cold water.

In the same pan you used for the nuts, now add @oil{1%tbsp} over a high heat. Add the asparagus and fry off for ~{3%minutes}, remove from the pan and reduce the heat to medium.

Mix the @soy sauce{1}, @yellow bean sauce{2}, @rice vinegar{1/2} and @water{3%tbsp}.

Add the whites of the spring onion, garlic, ginger and @sesame oil{1/2} to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the asparagus back to the pan along with the sauce and mix everything together. Add the drained noodles and broccoli and warm everything through.

Divide the stir fry between your #bowls{} and top with the toasted cashew nuts and the greens of the spring onions.